cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.NE 

The paper focuses on the evaluation of explainers for convolutional deep neural networks in the context of adversarial attacks in image classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of deep neural networks and their susceptibility to adversarial attacks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance of different explainers, which could place it in cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
